Not only are you a gifted writer, but you are &quot;Akicita Was`te,&quot; an honorable warrior, in the words of my Lakota people.  You have made Ronald something more than just a statistic for those of us that did not know him personnaly.  Thanks for sharing him, allowing me to see him through your preceptive eyes.  He is more than an HONORABLE MARINE... far more than a prestigious citation... he is &quot;Hunkapi&quot; everyone's relative, without need of ceremony.  I feel a huge sense of loss, which is certainly less than that which lives in your heart.  Good Luck! in locating the &quot;folks&quot; you seek.  I am sincerely grateful that you made it home.  The honor you give augments the honor that you deserve and receive from me and many others.  As an Army Captain (RVN 66-67-69) I was priviledged or cursed, however you choose to view it, to witness the sacrifice of so many.  I know what good men are made of.  I would have been blessed to have had a few good men like you and Bro. by my side.  In retrospect, I guess you were by my side, all the time.  Do not let those who were not there dilute the sacredness of your voice.  
